trans-unit.source: A path is hierarchical and composed of a sequence of directory and file name elements separated by a special separator or delimiter. A root component, that identifies a file system hierarchy, may also be present. The name element that is farthest from the root of the directory hierarchy is the name of a file or directory. The other name elements are directory names. A Path can represent a root, a root and a sequence of names, or simply one or more name elements. A Path is considered to be an empty path if it consists solely of one name element that is empty. Accessing a file using an empty path is equivalent to accessing the default directory of the process.
trans-unit.target: 路径是分层的，由一系列目录和文件名元素组成，并由特殊的分隔符或定界符分隔。也可能存在标识文件系统层次结构的根组件。离目录层次结构的根最远的name元素是文件或目录的名称。其他名称元素是目录名称。甲 Path 可以代表一个根，根和名称的序列，或只是一个或多个名称的元件。如果 Path 仅由一个空的名称元素组成，则将其视为空路径。使用空路径访问文件等效于访问进程的默认目录。

trans-unit.source: A response can be upgraded with the #upgrade method. Once invoked, headers are written and the connection IO (a socket) is yielded to the given block. The block must invoke #close afterwards, the server won't do it in this case. This is useful to implement protocol upgrades, such as websockets.
trans-unit.target: 可以使用 #upgrade 方法升级响应。调用后，将写入标头，并将连接 IO （套接字）产生到给定的块。该块必须随后调用 #close ，在这种情况下服务器不会执行该操作。这对于实现协议升级（例如websocket）很有用。

trans-unit.source: A server can be closed by calling #close. This closes the server sockets and stops processing any new requests, even on connections with keep-alive enabled. Currently processing requests are not interrupted but also not waited for. In order to give them some grace period for finishing, the calling context can add a timeout like sleep 10.seconds after #listen returns.
trans-unit.target: 可以通过调用 #close 来关闭服务器。这将关闭服务器套接字并停止处理任何新请求，即使在启用了保持活动的连接上也是如此。当前，处理请求不会中断，也不会等待。为了给他们一些宽限期来完成，调用上下文可以在 #listen 返回后的10 秒内添加一个超时，如 sleep 10.seconds 。
